-- NAB sells $1.9 bln UK commercial real estate loans
-- By Swati Pandey
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 04:59PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 16 (Reuters) - National Australia Bank <NAB.AX> on Tuesday said it will sell an additional 1.2 billion pounds ($1.88 billion) of mostly non-performing UK commercial property loans to private equity firm Cerberus Global Investors.

NAB, Australia's fourth largest bank by market value, has made exiting its UK operations a priority after writedowns for the troubled business led to a 10 percent decline in annual cash profit. [ID:nL4N0SO83K] In July, it had agreed to sell 625 million pounds of mostly non-performing UK commercial property loans.